In the provided Hangman game code, if a user enters a letter that has already been guessed correctly, the game simply treats it as a correct guess and continues. It does not explicitly inform the user that the letter has already been guessed, nor does it penalize the user for guessing the same letter again.

If you want to handle this scenario, you could modify the code to keep track of all guessed letters and check each new guess against this list. If a user tries to guess a letter that has already been guessed, the game could then inform the user and ask for a new guess.

